1. To avoid issues, run the following command once before working through the steps of a question. The command sets the context and the namespace at the same time:
$ kubectl config set-context <context-of-question> \  --namespace=<namespace-of-question>

2. Using an Alias for kubectl
$ alias k=kubectl
$ k version

3. Internalize Resource Short Names
$ kubectl api-resources

4. Delete objects right away
$ kubectl delete pod nginx --grace-period=0 --force

5. Find object info   -C 10 option to output 10 lines of context
$ kubectl describe pods | grep -C 10 "author=John Doe"
$ kubectl get pods -o yaml | grep -C 5 labels:

6. Explore fields of kubectl resources
$ kubectl explain pods.spec
